Stock Market Tracker:
This program uses the Yahoo Finance API (via HTTP) to fetch data.

Manual:
LED Color Logic (via Blynk Virtual Pins):
    - Blue  (V4): Market is closed
    - Green (V3): Current price > open price (market up)
    - Red   (V2): Current price < open price (market down)
    - Off       : Current price = open price 
    - Magenta   : Error (JSON, HTTPS, etc). Check Serial Monitor to debug.

LED Intensity: Scaled 0–255 based on % change (0%=0, >=2%=255)

Virtual Pin Mapping:
    V2 = Red   channel (0–255)
    V3 = Green channel (0–255)
    V4 = Blue  channel (0–255)
    V10 = Debug label (string)
    V11 = Price info string

Dependencies:
    - Go to File -> Preferences
    - Find the "Additional boards manager URLs" field and paste this URL:
        - http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json
    - Go to Tools -> Board -> Boards Manager
    - Search for esp8266
    - Install "esp8266 by ESP8266 Community"
    - Once installed, go back to Tools -> Board and you should now see a full list of ESP8266 boards — select "SparkFun ESP8266 Thing"

Libraries:
    - Go to Sketch -> Include Library -> Manage Libraries
    - Search up and install these two libraries
        - Blynk by Volodymyr Shymanskyy
        - ArduinoJson by Benoit Blanchon

How to use:
    - Fill out secrets.h
    - Add V2, V3, and V4 as virtual pins of type "integer", with min value of 0, and max value of 255
    - Add V10 and V11 as virtual pins of type "string"

Troubleshoot:
    - Check if Yahoo Finance API is working
        - https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v8/finance/chart/SPY?interval=1d&range=1d 
    - Go to Blynk Dashboard and add widgets
        - Value for V2, V3, V4, V10, and V11